result.execSummary:
The defendant Cordell M Howze was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Armed Robbery, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments and costs.  All financial obligations to be paid through collection of sums by DOC from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of Extended supervision. Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
Consecutive to: Consecutive to any other time.

superMiscConds.notes: Obtain/maintain full time employment,  or full time school and part time employment.
Mental health assessment. Successfully complete follow up treatment. Take any prescription medication only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician.
No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.

Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent.
Participate in cognitive thinking program.
Pay all supervision fees.

supervisions.notes:
Provide a DNA sample if not previously done so, pay surcharge.
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions: firearm possession and voting.

Matter before the Court for Final pre-trial.    Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  The Court orders uncharged offenses contained within Milwaukee police department incident reports (#140920020, 140500089, 140500030) read-in for the purpose of sentencing.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  

AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on state's motion, the Court ordered Count 2 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing in Count 1.

The Court orders the defendant REMANDED.  Jury trial set for 9-29-14 removed from the calendar at this time.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 16, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
